Gearbest is selling the Cubot X18 Plus at great discounts until 12 March, with free shipping to South Africa. The device is available for $79.99 for the first 10 units sold until 9 March and will then be priced at $129.99 until 12 March. From 13 March, it will be available on Gearbest.com at its normal price of $169.99. The device features a massive 5.99-inch display with a with a resolution of 2,160 x 1,080 for a wider field of vison and an immersive viewing experience. It also features dual rear cameras and a fingerprint scanner, and is powered by Google’s Android 8.0 operating system. The specifications of the Cubot X18 are detailed in the table below. The Cubot X18 has been unlocked for Worldwide use, but you should ensure that your local network is compatible before purchasing the device. If you are a first-time buyer and need assistance with your purchase, you can find Gearbest’s South African-based partner on the MyBroadband Forum as GearBestZA. For more information, visit the Gearbest website.   This article was published in partnership with Gearbest.